 your company’.</li><li>Attach the receipt to your application and submit it via the <a href=\"https://omgeving.vlaanderen.be/erkenningenloket\">online recognition desk of the Department of Environment and Spatial Development</a> (click on ‘Ga naar het erkenningenloket’; log in with e-ID). If you do not have a Belgian eID, you should submit your application by registered letter to Departement Omgeving, Koning Albert II-laan 20/bus 8, 1000 Brussel, to the attention of Team Erkenningen, afdeling GOP.</li></ol><p>The competent unit handles your application and takes a decision within 90 days, counting from the day after submission of the complete application file.</p><p>If your company meets the recognition conditions, the Energy and Climate Agency of Flanders will:</p><ul><li>issue a <strong>European certificate</strong> and a <strong>Flemish recognition certificate</strong></li><li>include the details of the company on the list of recognised fire protection equipment companies.</li></ul><h3><strong>Your company already holds a European certificate as a fire protection equipment company</strong></h3><p>A company that has already obtained a certificate as a fire protection equipment company outside the Flemish Region must register via the <a href=\"https://omgeving.vlaanderen.be/erkenningenloket\">online recognition desk of the Department of Environment and Spatial Development</a> (click on ‘Ga naar het erkenningenloket’; log in with eID).</p><p>If you do not have a Belgian eID, you should register the company by registered letter with the Flemish administration before being allowed to work in the Flemish Region. Send your notification by registered letter to Departement Omgeving, Koning Albert II-laan 20/bus 8, 1000 Brussel, to the attention of Team Erkenningen, afdeling GOP.</p><p>Attach the following information to your notification:</p><ul><li>a copy of the European certificate as a fire protection equipment company in Dutch, French, German or English</li><li>the o